Anonymous Sat 15 Apr 2023 21:24:48 No.55804870 Report
Quoted By: >>55804968 >>55806890
>>55804485
it's advertised as a soulslike, but my game experience so far is that it is much more story, character and decision focused than souls. Combat is soulslike insofar that keeping your distance and wating for opportunites is key, but it's much more forgiving and uses stuff like combos and special attacks.

Gameplay is not groundbreaking, but it's pretty solid and pleasant to work with. As I said, the game world is much more lively with actual characters and ditches the "zanzibart forgive me" bullshit in favor of laying out the lore, factions and the power struggle within the cursed city pretty clearly.

The aesthetic and stylisation is a nice change of pace from the usual grimdark souls ripoff. The Setting makes use of ancient greek inspirations and I thought it was pretty fun to listen to the various character's stances on ancient government and social hierarchies.

The steam reviews also hold it in high regards. It's a decent game and on sale at the moment.
